news.title: Indore: Residency area survey to help prepare new record of rights
news.para: According to collector Asheesh Singh, the entire Residency Area is un-surveyed and it has government and some private land. “We have completed land survey of Residency Area and after first notification, the process of new record of rights will be initiated,” he said.

news.title: More than five lakh properties in Nashik to get unique ID codes
news.para: Each property in the city will be given an identity code by the NMC. This will help the civic body access all details, including built-up area and other specifications related to the properties, at one click.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body offers interest rebate for property tax defaulters
news.para: For properties that fall under the old formula, a 100% interest rebate will be given to slum or chawl dwellers paying their tax dues, while a 75% rebate will be given to owners of flats, tenements and bungalows.

news.title: Builders get GST notices to reverse input tax credit
news.para: The notices were issued for the years 2017-18 and 2018-19. The department has asked builders to reverse the ITC for the unsold apartments at the time of procuring Building Use (BU) permission.

news.title: Several builders under income tax department's scanner in Mohali
news.para: According to the information, different I-T teams landed at the offices of builders located in Mohali and New Chandigarh early in the morning.

news.title: Trinity Infratech appoints Adil Altaf as Managing Director
news.para: Commenting on the appointment, Trinity’s senior management stated, "Adil's journey in real estate is marked by a series of achievements and milestones. He has a proven expertise in sales, marketing, and customer relationship management.

news.title: Private equity funds close in on deal to acquire Shriram Housing Finance
news.para: Parent Shriram Finance, which is mainly involved in commercial vehicle financing, owns 84.82% of Shriram Housing Finance Ltd, which focuses on affordable homes. San Francisco-based PE Valiant Capital Management owns most of the remaining stake.

news.title: Court refuses to extend interim medical bail of HDIL promoter in PMLA case
news.para: In November last year, the Supreme Court granted interim bail to the founder of Housing Development Infrastructure Limited (HDIL) on medical grounds in a predicate offence, linked to the PMLA case, that is being probed by the Economic Offences Wing (EOW) of Mumbai police.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body seals Rockline Mall over Rs 11.5 crore property tax due
news.para: Stating that around Rs 2 crore is being paid towards property tax for the mall as per the High Court’s direction, Venkatesh said he has already paid the property tax for the year 2023-24 and also intimated the BBMP about it.

news.title: Haryana RERA kicks off survey of stuck residential projects in Gurugram
news.para: According to H-Rera officials, Arun Kumar, chairman of the authority’s Gurgaon bench, ordered the survey to check the reality of the projects on the ground level and verify the claims being made by developers to avoid action.

news.title: Maharashtra government allocates Rs 145 crore for infra development in rural Nashik
news.para: “State govt has earmarked Rs 145 crore under special additional outlay for urban pockets in the district that includes all 15 councils and nagar panchayats. This will help these urban areas to carry out developmental works,” said Nashik DPO Kiran Joshi.

news.title: Liquidator’s now required to convene SCC meetings at interval of 30 days: IBBI
news.para: Among the key amendments, the liquidator can reduce the reserve price by up to 25 per cent for assets with existing valuation of the Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP) once during the liquidation process, provided it is approved by SCC.

news.title: Ensure financial service providers have regulatory nod for voluntary liquidation: IBBI to liquidators
news.para: FSPs notified by the central government after consulting financial regulators are allowed to undergo a voluntary liquidation process after obtaining prior permission of the appropriate regulator.

news.title: Slum policy benefits not for those filing GST, ITR: Allahabad HC
news.para: The bench of Justices Vivek Chaudhary and OP Shukla also directed the state govt, LDA and the petitioners to furnish the list of those dwellers, who file GST and Income Tax returns, along with the last two years' details.

news.title: Australia's Dexus records statutory net loss of A$597.2 million in July-December 2023
news.para: CEO Darren Steinberg said he believed the office sector was nearing the bottom, which should in turn help unfreeze a market that has seen very few sales as buyers wait to see how far prices will fall.

news.title: Shriram Properties' net profit dips 17.35% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Shriram Properties' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 240.57 crore in Q3 FY24, a growth of 8.36 per cent from Rs 222.01 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Seven years on, Nagpur smart city yet to finish works
news.para: Now, with just four months left for the Smart Cities Mission deadline, it seems a herculean task for the NSSCDCL to finish the pending works in time. The flagship mission involves development of 100 cities into smart cities.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects' net profit up 1.86% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,970.50 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 16.06 per cent from Rs 2,347.50 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: At least 60,000 houses to get underground drainage link in Madurai
news.para: Corporation officials told TOI that construction work will be completed in 36 months. The trial run of the system would be done for six months and maintenance will be carried out for the next 18 months by the contractor.

news.title: Allotted houses to stay out of liquidation: IBBI
news.para: According to one of the amendments by IBBI, wherever the corporate debtor has given possession to an allottee in a real estate project, such asset shall not form a part of the liquidation estate of the corporate debtor.
